	<config>
		<documentation>
Vantage InFusion driver - Installation

The Vantage Infusion drivers allow the Control4 system to work in conjunction with a Vantage InFusion system.  Note: They do not support the legacy Vantage QLink system which uses a different control protocol.

What Support You Should Expect to Receive

Control4 is not able to advise you or support you when configuring Vantage InFusion systems.  If your organization does not have a Vantage-trained programmer, you should enlist the help of a Vantage programmer - particularly for installations in customer environments. We will, by necessity, limit our support to the proper configuration of these drivers within the Control4 system.

How to Install and Configure the Drivers

The Control4 system on which you are installing these drivers must be running Release 1.7.0 or later.  Because these drivers are based on DriverWorks, they don't require a Release 1.8 system update.  There is no difference in the user experience based on underlying system version.

Prior to installing the Vantage InFusion drivers, verify that your system is functioning correctly. These drivers are included in Releases  1.8.2 and 1.7.4.  However, they can be installed manually on other version systems.

The following steps give an overview of the installation process. 
1.  Add the Vantage InFusion Network driver to your project [System Design, Search, Local Database, --others--, Vantage InFusion]
2.  Configure the Vantage InFusion Network driver for serial or TCP/IP connection to the Vantage system.  
  a.  If you are using a TCP/IP connection, Enter the IP Address of the Vantage System in the Identify dialog . 
  b.  If you are using a serial connection, configure the serial port binding [Connections, Control/AV]. 
3.  Add/configure the specific dimmer, switch, keypad, and task drivers as needed based on the system you're connected to [System Design, Search, Local Database, ...]
  * Dimmer [Light, Vantage Dimmer]
  * Switch [Light, Vantage Switch]
  * Keypad [--others--, Vantage Keypad]
  * Task [--others--, Vantage Task]
4.  If desired, further integrate the Vantage system with the Control4 system using one or more of the following capabilities:
  * Binding [Connections, Control/AV, Button Link]
  * Lighting Scenes [Agents, Lighting Scenes] 
  * Programming (events, conditionals, actions) [Programming]
5.  Make sure you Refresh Navigators after configuring the system


Vantage Dimmer Driver

The Vantage Dimmer driver is used to control and monitor any dimmer on a Vantage Infusion system. One driver should be added for each load that is controlled or monitored. When the driver is added it is automatically linked to a Vantage Infusion driver if it exists. If the driver does not exist the connection will need to be made manually after it has been added.
The Vantage Dimmer Driver will also control and monitor Vantage Groups.

Properties

Vantage Device ID:	
This is the vantage id of the dimmer to control. This is how it is identified. The Vantage ID can be found by using Vantage Design Center.

Click Ramp Rate Up:	
This parameter specifies the number of seconds for the light to ramp up.

Click Ramp Rate Down:	
This parameter specifies the number of seconds for the light to ramp down.

Hold Ramp Rate Up:	
This parameter specifies the number of seconds for the light to ramp up while being held.

Hold Ramp Rate Down:	
This parameter specifies the number of seconds for the light to ramp down while being held.

Debug Mode:
Used for debugging the driver. Output is displayed on the Lua tab.
Options:
    Off
    Print
    Log
    Print and Log

Variables
Same as the C4 Light Proxy.

Events
The Vantage Dimmer has no buttons attached to the dimmer. There are therefore no associations between a button and a dimmer. Level Changes is the only event for a Vantage Dimmer.

Commands
All of the C4 Light Proxy non button commands are supported.

Conditionals
All of the C4 Light Proxy Conditions.

Loops
All of the C4 Light Proxy Loops.

Connnections
The following connections are available:
*  ON Button Link
*  OFF Button Link
*  Toggle Button Link
		</documentation>
